# HTML & CSS Guidelines

## HTML Standards

- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Ensure accessibility with proper ARIA labels and semantic markup
- Include proper meta tags and viewport settings
- Use meaningful alt text for images

## CSS Standards

- Implement responsive design with CSS Grid/Flexbox
- Support both light and dark modes using CSS custom properties
- Use CSS variables for consistent theming
- Follow BEM methodology for CSS class naming
- Keep popup width at 300px for consistency

## UI/UX Principles

- Use modern, clean design with subtle shadows and rounded corners
- Implement smooth transitions and hover effects
- Provide clear visual feedback for user actions
- Use SVG icons for crisp display at all sizes
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for accessibility

## Theme Support

- Define CSS custom properties for colors
- Use `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` for automatic theme detection
- Implement smooth transitions for theme changes
- Test both light and dark mode appearances
